Davido’s Personal Logistic Manager, Israel DMW, has opened up to him on the fracas that ensued between him and an airport official. A few days ago the controversial aide was caught on camera exchanging blows with an unidentified airport official. According to an eyewitness, who made the video, a scuffle ensued after Israel refused to pay the airport official N1,500 for carrying his luggage.   True love must feel like my grandma’s love –…     Cubana Priest rains money on Rick Ross     Icezy sets to release new single ‘Body Riddim’   In a new video which surfaced online days later, the DMW boss could be heard asking his personal aide why he spat on someone’s face at the airport. Davido who spoke Pidgin said: “Why you go spit for person face?” Responding, Isreal stated he gave the airport official N1,500 but he requested for more as he noted the sum was too little. Angered by the fellow’s attitude, Isreal DMW said he requested for the money back but the airport official refused to return it which eventually led to the fight. “My oga, that guy messed up. I dash you money, you dey tell me say e no reach. You work for me? 1,500 na small money?” said Israel